# Deploy to GitHub (Vida Sobre Ruedas)

Use this workflow whenever the user asks to deploy or push this project.

- Repository URL must be `https://github.com/Janick18/Vida-Sobre-Ruedas.git`.
- Confirm current directory is project root and run `git status` first.
- If `origin` is missing, add it with `git remote add origin <repo-url>`.
- Ensure branch is `main` using `git branch -M main`.
- Stage and commit only when user requested a commit.
- Push with `git push -u origin main`.
- If push fails due to auth, do not ask for tokens in chat. Instruct user to authenticate locally with Git credential helper or SSH.
- Never print, store, or echo Personal Access Tokens.

Quick command sequence:

```bash
git status
git remote -v
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```
